üì¨ What is Letter Writing for Sweepstakes?

Many sweepstakes and contest websites offer an Alternative Method of Entry (AMOE), such as handwritten letters or mail-in submissions, allowing participants to enter without making a purchase. This method benefits both the sweepstakes operators and participants:

  • For sweepstakes websites: AMOE helps them comply with legal regulations (such as gambling tax exemptions) by providing a free entry option.
  • For participants: It's a way to enter and earn SC without spending money‚Äîwhich lets you cash out to Real Life Money.
  • Earning potential: Each handwritten letter submission can earn you $5 per letter in SC credits that convert to real cash.

By leveraging our automated system, we help you earn through Letter Writing and increase your profit while saving you time and effort.

‚öôÔ∏è How Our Service Works

Each sweepstakes website has Official Rules outlining specific requirements for mail-in entries. These often include:

  • Letter size and format (e.g., postcard vs. envelope)
  • Handwriting specifications (some require legible, handwritten text)
  • Pen color restrictions (e.g., only blue or black ink)
  • Entry limits per envelope (some allow multiple entries per submission)

Our service handles all these details for you, ensuring every submission meets the exact guidelines so you don't have to worry about disqualifications.
